  "name": "Jeanne d'Arc",
  "title": "Maiden of Radiance",
  "secondName": "Maiden of Radiance",
  "description": "Though Jeanne often stayed in the shadow of her sister, the village noticed her piety. She obeyed the church's teachings, prayed often, and helped who she could in her own shy way. Many suspected she would become the priestess's acolyte when she came of age, just as they said Mikaela would join the holy army.\n\nSadly, neither would come to pass.\n\nWhen the war took a turn for the worse, their village found itself alone in the dark, without defense. Jeanne and Mikaela ran for the church together, hoping that if they reached its sacred ground, they'd be safe.\n\nThey were right: the demons couldn't breach the church. But only Jeanne made it there alive.",
